@Reasoning:
This is the primary external-API entry point; the name reflects the abstract operation rather than the internal emitter mechanics. We deliberately allocate a fresh emitter per call so callers using the public API don't have to think about lifecycle management.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_from_makefile" that takes makefile_source as String returns Integer:
    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter
    Return proc makefile_to_hir_with_emitter with emitter_ptr, makefile_source
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric to translate_from_makefile but for the HIR-to-source direction; both share the same per-call emitter creation convention so neither requires lifecycle knowledge from external callers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_to_makefile" that takes hir_root as Integer returns String:
    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter
    Return proc hir_to_makefile_with_emitter with emitter_ptr, hir_root
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validation is parsing without semantic analysis or HIR generation; the parse_makefile return value (1/0) is already the validation answer. We use a temporary emitter so the validator is safe to call from any context (e.g., a lint hook) without affecting other in-flight translations.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_makefile" that takes makefile_source as String returns Integer:
    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter
    Let parse_success be proc parse_makefile with emitter_ptr, makefile_source

    Return parse_success
End Process
